abstract: >
  This repository provides a minimal, executable reference implementation
  of a governed scientific claim lifecycle integrated with a deterministic
  enforcement engine (CRI-CORE). It demonstrates evidence-driven state
  transitions, structural run artifact contracts, role separation
  enforcement, SHA256-based integrity verification, and centralized
  commit gating via explicit enforcement decisions. The project isolates
  lifecycle semantics from enforcement logic to illustrate how claim
  mutation can be restricted to validated transition attempts under
  reproducible governance constraints.

